        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> I try to keep complaining to a minimum.  I love my class and I love the game.  Yet one thing has always bugged me playing a necro.  As most people know, a necromancer is basically liching full-time when fighting.  My problem is that when liching all unique appearances of your character and equipment are totally lost. Personally, I would like to look different than my pet and all the other necros and their pets. Even weapons are hidden when arch-liching.  Furthermore, I am a gnome, and skeleton and spectre forms are not relevant to the size of the character.</P><P>Ideal Solution:<BR>I have always thought it would be very sweet if verrant created a unique lich model (that displayed equipment) for every race and possibly for every face of each race.  This way players could maintain individuality and at the same time proudly display visible equipment.  I was thinking that when these models were drawn they would appear like your characters face only in a state of undead decay with glowing eyes.  Maybe this model would be reserved for arch-lich? Possibly lower level liches could be skeletons that showed equipments graphics?</P><P>Zorlak</P><P> </font></td>

